Marriner Stoddard Eccles, born September 9, 1890 in Logan. Utah, who died December 18, 1977 in Salt Lake City, Utah, was an American banker and economist. He was Chairman of the Federal Reserve of the United States (the American central bank) from November 15, 1934 to April 14, 1948 under the presidencies of Roosevelt and Truman.
